de.mrapp.android.util.view

Class AbstractSavedState

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.mrapp.android.util.view.AbstractSavedState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable

    public abstract class AbstractSavedState
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable
    An abstract base class for all data structures, which allow to store the internal state of a view. This class identical to the class AbsSavedState of the Android SDK, except for the fact, that it does use a custom class loader instead of the system's one. The reason for this is, that using the class AbsSavedState in a library project, may cause a BadParcelableException to be thrown when unmarshalling.
    Since:
    1.8.0
